The paper discusses a method for analyzing the reliability and performance of software systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The method involves using domain-specific modeling patterns, which suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The method also involves precomputing closed-form expressions, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses reducing analysis time, which suggests a focus on optimization and operations research (cs.LO).
